          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two U samples were integrated in the central hole of",
                "the cathode  plates. They both consisted of 500 mu-",
                "g/cm2 of uranium (235UF4),  evaporated on a 30 mu-m",
                "Al backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector configuration consisted of",
                "a Frisch-gridded, twin ionization chamber with two",
                "supplementary solid-state detectors. The anode",
                "plates had a circular hole in the middle, which was",
                "covered only by a thin Au-evaporated polyimide ton.",
                "This allowed the gas detector to be used as a",
                "transmission section. Surface-barrier detectors (PIPS,",
                " 500 mu-m depletion) were  placed closely behind",
                "the partially transparent  anodes. They acted as stop",
                "detectors. An asymmetric  setup was used, with a thin",
                "dE part (15 mm) on one  side and a larger (25 mm) on",
                "the other. The  detection chamber was filled with",
                "99.995% pure CH4  gas, kept at a constant pressure",
                "of 3 +- 0.05 bar,  with a low gas flow."
              ]
            }
          ],
